-- Mexico Stocks: Compartamos, Industrias Penoles Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-03-02T22:06:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/mexico-stocks-compartamos-industrias-penoles-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. Mexico City time.  The IPC  index  rose 0.8 percent to 38,327.43.  Compartamos SAB (COMPARC*)  (COMPARC* MM), the holding company that
controls low-income lender Banco Compartamos SA, slipped 2.7
percent to 13.79 pesos. The market is “disappointed” by the
company’s guidance this week, Rafael Escobar, an analyst with
Mexico City-based Vector Casa de Bolsa SA, said in a phone
interview today. Compartamos said Feb. 29 that net income would
rise between 2 percent and 5 percent this year.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, sank 0.7 percent to 647.93 pesos. Silver
futures for May delivery fell in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
